text: The Alabama Senate is the upper house of the Alabama Legislature, the state legislature of the U.S. state of Florida, the Alabama House of Representatives being the lower house.https://apnews.com/article/al-state-wire-alabama- lifestyle-legislature-gun-politics-1e5fde68e5c4937a49d1fc76b14372f5 The Senate is made of 35 members, each elected from a single-member district with a population of about 125,000 people. , Republicans hold the majority in the chamber with 27 seats; Democrats are in the minority with 6 seats. ==References== Category:State upper houses in the United States Category:Alabama Legislature
title: Alabama Senate
